videoSnippet.title: Grischuk Beats Magnus Carlsen in 7 Moves (Chess960) - Well Played, Sir :)
videoSnippet.description:

Alexander Grischuk VS Magnus Carlsen
Speedchess Championship Semi-finals
21.11.2017 on Chess.com

1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 Bg4 3. Bg2 c6 4. O-O Nd7 5. d3 e6 6. e4 Bd6 7. h3 Bh5 8. exd5 exd5 9. Qe1+ Ne7 10. Nh4 O-O 11. g4 Re8 12. gxh5 Nc8 13. Qd1 Qxh4 14. Qg4 Qd8 15. h6 g6 16. c4 Ne5 17. Qd1 dxc4 18. dxc4 Nb6 19. Nc3 Nexc4 20. Ne4 Be5 21. Qf3 f5 22. Ng5 Bxb2 23. Bf4 Bxa1 24. Rxa1 Qf6 25. Rc1 Rad8 26. h4 Rd4 27. Qc3 Rd1+ 28. Kh2 Qxc3 29. Rxc3 Rd4 30. Kg3 Red8 31. Bf1 Rxf4

Magnus Carlsen is the first player to reach the final of the 2017 Chess.com Speed Chess Championship. On Tuesday the world champion beat Alexander Grischuk with a five-point margin despite losing the bullet segment.

This week's match was the complete opposite of last year's Grandmaster Blitz Battle between the same players, when Carlsen had a rusty start but crushed his opponent in the bullet.

Yesterday, from the get go Carlsen was cruising, and yet another dominating performance was looming. Winning the 5|2 portion with a 6-2 score (and good chess), he continued the great form he had shown half a week earlier in his match with Wesley So and against Ding Liren at the Champions Showdown.

But this time, Carlsen couldn't keep the pace.
